videos.description: Khadeen Carrington gets inside for a nice basket to put Seton Hall ahead 38-37 at the end of the first half against Louisville.
videos.headline: Carrington gets nice bucket to put Seton Hall ahead at halftime

videos.description: Deng Adel swats away Khadeen Carrington's shot and takes it down the court for a nice layup in the first half.
videos.headline: Louisville's Adel denies Carrington at the rim

videos.description: Desi Rodriguez recovers a loose ball and sinks a jumper, giving him 21 points early in the second half.
videos.headline: Rodriguez makes nice jumper for Seton Hall

videos.description: Louisville takes its largest lead of the game after a 3-pointer from Dwayne Sutton, which was followed by a quick layup from Quentin Snider.
videos.headline: Louisville answers with back-to-back buckets

videos.description: Dwayne Sutton finds V.J. King who sinks a nice 3-pointer from the corner in the second half.
videos.headline: Louisville's King knocks down a triple

videos.description: Khadeen Carrington gets a pass from down court and lays it up while drawing the foul for a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Carrington makes tough layup and draws the foul

videos.description: Ismael Sanogo intercepts a pass and then flushes it down on the other end forcing Louisville to call a timeout.
videos.headline: Sanogo gets steal and slam for Seton Hall

videos.description: Quentin Snider is defended by Seton Hall's Khadeen Carrington and shows off his handles before knocking down a nice 3-pointer in the second half.
videos.headline: Louisville's Snider shows off handles

videos.description: Myles Powell adds to Seton Hall's lead late in the fourth quarter against No. 17 Louisville with a three pointer.
videos.headline: Powell makes deep 3-pointer to energize Seton Hall

videos.description: Desi Rodriguez makes a tough layup in the final seconds of the game to give Seton Hall a 79-77 win over Louisville.
videos.headline: Rodriguez gets layup in traffic to upset No. 17 Louisville

videos.description: Desi Rodriguez gets through traffic and makes a tricky basket in the last seven seconds of the game. Seton Hall defeats No. 17 Louisville 79-77.
videos.headline: Seton Hall's Rodriguez banks in layup for the win
